Please tell me more about J. D. Salinger's books and his major themes.

J.D. Salinger was an American writer, best known for his novel "The Catcher in the Rye," published in 1951. Born on January 1, 1919, Jerome David Salinger was raised in Manhattan and spent most of his life writing from seclusion in rural New Hampshire. Apart from "The Catcher in the Rye," he also wrote a series of short stories featuring the fictional Glass family.

Some significant works by J.D. Salinger include:

1. The Catcher In The Rye (1951) - This novel follows Holden Caulfield, a teenage boy who is expelled from school and goes through a series of adventures before returning home to face his reality.
